Scott Hanson, the host of NFL RedZone on NFL Network, is a very enthusiastic person, which makes watching him jump from big play to big play on Sundays so much fun.

Well, he had a really wild moment Sunday when two games – Steelers vs. Jags and Texans vs. Redskins – had two big plays in the final seconds.

Enjoy it:

How great was that? The Steelers interception, however, was called back due to a Jaguars penalty and the Redskins’ field goal didn’t actually hit the bar, instead it landed a few yards short in the end zone. Hanson noticed that on the replay and apologized profusely, saying it was an optical illusion.

Twitter had no problem forgiving him for that mistake and celebrating his enthusiasm:

@ScottHanson it's okay man I thought the ball hit the crossbar too lol — Jamie J (@__MrJay) November 18, 2018

@ScottHanson that was the greatest call of something that did not happen ever😀 LOVE IT!!! — Big Fan (@Badgers89_) November 18, 2018

@ScottHanson thought the exact same thing on the Hopkins kick, no worries! #opticalillusions — CAV (@Vanetti_for_3) November 18, 2018

@ScottHanson no worries, looked the same for us 😂 — Dominic Neumayr (@dneymar4) November 18, 2018

@ScottHanson I’m yelling with you on that Washington FG 😂 — Nicholas Hawley (@NickHolla) November 18, 2018

My favourite thing about @RedZoneChannel is when @ScottHanson also gets the optical illusion wrong with me 😂🙏👌 so good. REPLAY. #redzone — Carl Dawkins (@carldawkinsbass) November 18, 2018

@ScottHanson your voice cracking for 2 plays in a row with that missed 64 yard field goal made my day. Thank you — Brutas Sacrifice III (@BrutasSacrifice) November 18, 2018

@ScottHanson is going nuts right now with all these games on Redzone…there is no better way to watch football on Sundays — Michael Thompson (@MThompson35) November 18, 2018

@ScottHanson That Wsh 63yd FG definitely looked like it hit the crossbar. You’re not crazy good sir! — CJ Donofrio (@CJisBallin) November 18, 2018

No one has as much fun on Sundays as @ScottHanson — Zachary Statham (@realzachstatham) November 18, 2018

Scott Hanson’s brain is melting on live TV — Kevin Glueck (@kevin_glueck) November 18, 2018

The enthusiasm and excitement of @ScottHanson is what makes Red Zone such essential viewing. — Sam Farley (@FarleyWrites) November 18, 2018
